Executive Profile
Frank A. Bozich  President & Chief Executive Officer, SI Group, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships57--
Background

		Mr. Frank A. Bozich has been the Chief Executive Officer and President at SI Group, Inc. since May 28, 2013. Mr. Bozich served as President of Global Catalysts Division at BASF Corporation since August 2010. He also founded Apex Adhesives, which was sold to Croda in 1993. Mr. Bozich has more than 20 years of industry experience, serving as Senior Vice President, Precious and Base Metal Services, for the Catalyst division. He joined BASF as part of acquisition of Engelhard ... Corporation in 2006. where he served as Group Vice President of Precious and Base Metal Services, Ventures and Enterprise Technologies and Group Vice President, Integration Management Office. Before joining Engelhard, he served as the General Manager European Region, Adhesives and Sealants, of the Rohm and Haas Company. He has been a Director of OGE Energy Corp since February 2016. Prior to joining Rohm and Haas, he spent five years with Croda Adhesives, Inc. in Itasca, Illinois, where Mr. Bozich served as President. He serves as a Director of Oklahoma Gas and Electric Company. He serves as Member of Supervisory Board at hte GmbH (hte Aktiengesellschaft). He has been an Additional Director of SI Group – India Limited since October 10, 2013. He served as a Board Member of Sion Power Corporation. Mr. Bozich holds a Bachelor's degree in Chemistry and a Master's degree in Business Administration from the University of Chicago, as well as a Master's degree in Chemistry from the University of Illinois.Read Full Background




